10 restitution or reparation should be recommended, the court shall make its recommendation a part
11 of the order committing the defendant to custody. The recommendation shall be in accordance
12 with the applicable provisions of G.S. 15A-1343(d) and Article 81C of Chapter 15A of the
13 General Statutes. If the offense is one in which there is evidence of physical, mental or sexual
14 abuse of a minor, the court may order the defendant to pay from work release earnings the cost
15 of rehabilitative treatment for the minor. The Administrative Office of the Courts shall prepare
16 and distribute forms which provide ample space to make restitution or reparation
17 recommendations incident to commitments, which forms shall be conveniently structured to
18 enable the sentencing court to make its recommendation.
19 (d) The Secretary of the Department of Adult Correction shall establish rules and
20 regulations to implement this section, which shall include adequate notice to the prisoner
21 incarcerated individual that the payment of restitution or reparation from any earnings gained by
22 the prisoner incarcerated individual while on work release is being considered as a condition of
23 any work-release privileges granted the prisoner, incarcerated individual, and opportunity for the
24 prisoner incarcerated individual to be heard. Such These rules and regulations shall also provide
25 additional methods whereby facts may be obtained to supplement the recommendation of the
26 sentencing court.
27 "§ 148-36. Secretary of the Department of Adult Correction to control classification and
28 operation of prison facilities.
29 All facilities established or acquired by the Division of Prisons of the Department of Adult
30 Correction shall be under the administrative control and direction of the Secretary of the
31 Department of Adult Correction, and operated under rules and regulations proposed by the
32 Secretary and adopted by the Division of Prisons of the Department of Adult Correction as
33 provided in G.S. 148-11. Subject to such these rules and regulations, the Secretary shall classify
34 the facilities of the State prison system and develop a variety of programs so as to permit proper
35 segregation and treatment of prisoners incarcerated individuals according to the nature of the
36 offenses committed, the character and mental condition of the prisoners, incarcerated individuals,
37 and such other factors as should be considered in providing an individualized system of
38 discipline, care, and correctional treatment of persons committed to the Division. The Secretary
39 of the Department of Adult Correction, or his the Secretary's authorized representative, shall
40 designate the places of confinement where sentences to imprisonment in the State's prison system
41 shall be served. The Secretary or his the Secretary's representative may designate any available
42 facility appropriate for the individual in view of custodial and correctional considerations.
43 "§ 148-37. Additional facilities authorized; contractual arrangements.
44 (a) Subject to the provisions of G.S. 143-341, the Division of Prisons of the Department
45 of Adult Correction may establish additional facilities for use by the Division, such these
46 facilities to be either of a permanent type of construction or of a temporary or movable type as
47 the Division may find most advantageous to the particular needs, to the end that the prisoners
48 incarcerated individuals under its supervision may be so distributed throughout the State as to
49 facilitate individualization of treatment designed to prepare them the incarcerated individuals for
50 lawful living in the community where they are each is most likely to reside after their release
51 from prison. For this purpose, the Division may purchase or lease sites and suitable lands adjacent
