10 "§ 148-40. Recapture of escaped prisoners.incarcerated individuals.
11 The rules and regulations for the government of the State prison system may provide for the
12 recapture of convicts incarcerated individuals that may escape, or any convicts incarcerated
13 individuals that may have escaped from the State's prison or prison camps, or county road camps
14 of this State, and the Division of Prisons of the Department of Adult Correction may pay to any
15 person recapturing an escaped convict such incarcerated individual a reward or expense of
16 recapture as the regulations may provide. Any citizen of North Carolina shall have authority to
17 apprehend any convict incarcerated individual who may escape before the expiration of the
18 convict's incarcerated individual's term of imprisonment whether the convict incarcerated
19 individual be guilty of a felony or misdemeanor, and retain the convict incarcerated individual in
20 custody and deliver the convict incarcerated individual to the Division of Prisons of the
21 Department of Adult Correction.
22 "§ 148-41. Recapture of escaping prisoners; incarcerated individuals; reward.
23 The Secretary of the Department of Adult Correction shall use every means possible to
24 recapture, regardless of expense, any prisoners incarcerated individuals escaping from or leaving
25 without permission any of the State prisons, camps, or farms. When any person who has been
26 confined or placed to work escapes from the State prison system, the Secretary shall immediately
27 notify the Governor, and accompany the notice with a full description of the escaped prisoner,
28 incarcerated individual, together with such information as will aid in the recapture. The Governor
29 may offer such rewards as he the Governor may deem desirable and necessary for the recapture
30 and return to the State prison system of any person who may escape or who heretofore has
31 escaped therefrom. Such escaped. The reward earned shall be paid by warrant of the Division of
32 Prisons of the Department of Adult Correction and accounted for as a part of the expense of
33 maintaining the State's prisons.
34 "§ 148-44. Separation as to sex.
35 The Department shall provide quarters for female prisoners incarcerated individuals separate
36 from those for male prisoners.incarcerated individuals.
37 "§ 148-45. Escaping or attempting escape from State prison system; failure of conditionally
38 and temporarily released prisoners incarcerated individuals and certain
39 youthful offenders to return to custody of Division of Prisons of the Department
40 of Adult Correction.
41 (a) Any person in the custody of the Division of Prisons of the Department of Adult
42 Correction in any of the classifications hereinafter set forth in this subsection who shall escape
43 from the State prison system, shall for the first such offense, except as provided in subsection (g)
44 of this section, be guilty of a Class 1 misdemeanor:
45 (1) A prisoner An incarcerated individual serving a sentence imposed upon
46 conviction of a misdemeanor;misdemeanor.
47 (2) A person who has been charged with a misdemeanor and who has been
48 committed to the custody of the Division of Prisons of the Department of
49 Adult Correction under the provisions of G.S. 162-39;G.S. 162-39.
